subSubSection.paragraph:
Coloration and morphology.
Body with coloration sheeny brown-black. Head in dorsal view with two pairs of angulate marginal projections between eyes and apex; frons (
Fig. 6
) produced to short, compressed, slightly curved horn at base and furnished in middle with two small tubercles; frons and clypeus area convex. Pronotum (
Fig. 4
) usually with median longitudinal ridge; middle of anterior margin of pronotum triangularly produced. Scutellum (
Figs. 7, 8
) divided into three parts: anterior part disklike with two pairs of small tubercles; middle part elevated with center obviously hollowed out and more laterally compressed and elevated on both sides; posterior part lower than middle region, furnished near apex with conical tubercle. Abdomen (
Fig. 9
) broader than tegmina; strongly depressed and all sternites lateral margins strongly expanded into dentations.
